{"ts":"2026-06-27T21:50:09.585Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Finalizing Download Logic**\n\nI'm now putting the finishing touches on the document download logic, and am handling the case where the file is not found. I've successfully implemented the streaming of the file content from S3 using the `s3_storage.download_file()` method, which handles any file not found errors. Now, the `GET /download/{id}` route returns a `StreamingResponse` for efficient file delivery, correctly setting the `Content-Disposition` header with the filename. I also considered and am now using the more straightforward `Response` object instead of `StreamingResponse`.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
