{"ts":"2026-06-27T21:50:22.598Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Designing the API Router**\n\nI'm making good headway designing the `backend/app/api/routes/documents.py` router. The plan includes a secure, multipart document upload via `POST /upload`. It will take a `UploadFile` and require thoughtful validation, which will include authorization and input cleaning before storage. I am now exploring security considerations around file uploads.\n\n\n**Refining Input Validation**\n\nI've refined the input validation for the document upload route. I now handle authorization by checking the user's role and client ID. Admins and GFF Admins have unrestricted upload access. Client users can only upload to their own client, enforced by checking `current_user.client_id` against the submitted `client_id`. This also takes into account optional fields.\n\n\n**Implementing Document ID Generation**\n\nI've decided to leverage `portal_items_repo._get_next_id(\"DOCUMENT\")` for thread-safe and consistent `document_id` generation, ensuring it aligns with our existing system. I'm now implementing the S3 upload using the generated ID.\n\nI'm calculating the `sha256` hash, formatting the file size, and inserting a `DOCUMENT` record into `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS` via the `portal_items_repo`. After considering the implications, I'll also insert a new `DocumentItem` into the SQLite database, mirroring existing route handler interactions.\n\n\n**Finalizing Database Integration**\n\nI've just finalized the database integration. My code now constructs a `DocumentItem` with a comprehensive set of fields including ID, client, project, title (defaulting to the filename), document type, status, version, owner, visibility, SHA256 hash, file size, description, and S3 URI. This data is then added to the SQLite database and committed. I've also added a refresh to make sure the object is up to date, to integrate cleanly with queries.\n\n\n**Ensuring Database Synchronization**\n\nI'm now laser-focused on ensuring perfect database synchronization after document uploads. I realized a potential issue with the `_sqlite_synced` flag and the caching of `sync_with_sqlite`. To ensure bulletproof consistency, I'll now explicitly write to both the SQLite database and `portal_items_repo` upon upload, completely bypassing the potential caching issue and ensuring the record exists in both repositories. This approach is exceptionally safe. I've also just started writing out the complete `POST /upload` route logic, starting with the necessary FastAPI imports for multipart file handling. I'm checking the parameter list next.\n\n\n**Calculating File Size & Hash**\n\nI've clarified how I'll calculate file size using `await file.read()` and `len(file_bytes)`, formatting it as KB or MB. I'll also compute the SHA256 hash using `hashlib`. I've also pivoted to implementing a `GET /download/{id}` endpoint and I'm ensuring client user access is restricted to their own documents within this route.\n\n\n**Implementing Download Endpoint**\n\nI'm now implementing the `/download/{id}` endpoint. I realized a key detail: I needed to fetch the document record and now know that I can't fetch it from DynamoDB initially, as the `client_id` is unknown at first. So, I will instead scan all documents or query by ID using the `portal_items_repo`. This is easy for MVP, because the MOCK_DB is instantaneous, and the code is simpler! I'm now implementing the access control logic, which involves a robust permission check.\n\n\n**Finalizing Download Logic**\n\nI'm now putting the finishing touches on the document download logic, and am handling the case where the file is not found. I've successfully implemented the streaming of the file content from S3 using the `s3_storage.download_file()` method, which handles any file not found errors. Now, the `GET /download/{id}` route returns a `StreamingResponse` for efficient file delivery, correctly setting the `Content-Disposition` header with the filename. I also considered and am now using the more straightforward `Response` object instead of `StreamingResponse`.\n\n\n**Adding the List Endpoint**\n\nI've just added a `GET /` list endpoint to the document router. The endpoint enforces client boundaries, ensuring that client users can only view documents associated with their own client ID. Admins and GFF Admins have unrestricted access. I'm also ensuring that the database query for the `list_items` function will work as expected, using either a `client_id` parameter, or the current user's `client_id`.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T21:50:22.602Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"dcpq6iib","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/backend/app/api/routes/documents.py","new_text":"from fastapi import APIRouter, Depends, HTTPException, status, UploadFile, File, Form, Response\nfrom typing import List, Optional\nimport hashlib\nimport datetime\n\nfrom ...db.session import get_db\nfrom ...models.user import User\nfrom ...models.document_item import DocumentItem\nfrom ...api.deps import get_current_user\nfrom ...repositories.portal_items import portal_items_repo\nfrom ...services.s3_storage import s3_storage\n\nrouter = APIRouter()\n\n@router.get(\"\")\ndef list_documents(\n    client_id: Optional[int] = None,\n    db = Depends(get_db),\n    current_user: User = Depends(get_current_user)\n):\n    \"\"\"\n    List GFF portal items of type DOCUMENT.\n    Strictly scopes non-admin users to their assigned client_id.\n    \"\"\"\n    target_client_id = client_id\n    if current_user.role not in [\"admin\", \"gff_admin\"]:\n        if current_user.client_id is None:\n            raise HTTPException(\n                status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN,\n                detail=\"User does not belong to any client account.\"\n            )\n        if target_client_id is not None and target_client_id != current_user.client_id:\n            raise HTTPException(\n                status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN,\n                detail=\"Access denied to requested client's documents.\"\n            )\n        target_client_id = current_user.client_id\n\n    cid_str = str(target_client_id) if target_client_id is not None else None\n    docs = portal_items_repo.list_items(\"DOCUMENT\", client_id=cid_str)\n    return [d.to_dict() for d in docs]\n\n\n@router.get(\"/{id}\")\ndef get_document(\n    id: int,\n    db = Depends(get_db),\n    current_user: User = Depends(get_current_user)\n):\n    \"\"\"\n    Retrieve document metadata by ID with strict client scoping.\n    \"\"\"\n    documents = portal_items_repo.list_items(\"DOCUMENT\")\n    doc = next((d for d in documents if str(d.id) == str(id)), None)\n    if not doc:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=status.HTTP_404_NOT_FOUND,\n            detail=\"Document not found.\"\n        )\n\n    # Scoping boundary check\n    if current_user.role not in [\"admin\", \"gff_admin\"]:\n        if str(doc.client_id) != str(current_user.client_id):\n            raise HTTPException(\n                status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN,\n                detail=\"Access denied. You do not have permission to view this document.\"\n            )\n\n    return doc.to_dict()\n\n\n@router.post(\"/upload\", status_code=201)\nasync def upload_document(\n    file: UploadFile = File(...),\n    client_id: int = Form(...),\n    project_id: Optional[int] = Form(None),\n    title: Optional[str] = Form(None),\n    document_type: Optional[str] = Form(None),\n    version: str = Form(\"1.0.0\"),\n    visibility: str = Form(\"private\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = Form(None),\n    db = Depends(get_db),\n    current_user: User = Depends(get_current_user)\n):\n    \"\"\"\n    Secure multi-part upload. Writes files to S3 (or mock local disk)\n    and saves document metadata in GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS and SQLite DB.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Authorization check\n    if current_user.role not in [\"admin\", \"gff_admin\"]:\n        if current_user.client_id is None or current_user.client_id != client_id:\n            raise HTTPException(\n                status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN,\n                detail=\"You do not have permission to upload documents for this client.\"\n            )\n\n    # Read file content\n    file_content = await file.read()\n    if not file_content:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=status.HTTP_400_BAD_REQUEST,\n            detail=\"Uploaded file is empty.\"\n        )\n\n    # Format filesize\n    size_kb = len(file_content) / 1024\n    if size_kb > 1024:\n        file_size_str = f\"{size_kb / 1024:.1f} MB\"\n    else:\n        file_size_str = f\"{size_kb:.1f} KB\"\n\n    # Calculate SHA-256 for cryptographic ledger sealing\n    sha256_hash = f\"0x{hashlib.sha256(file_content).hexdigest().upper()}\"\n\n    # Determine unique document ID\n    document_id = portal_items_repo._get_next_id(\"DOCUMENT\")\n\n    # Upload to S3 storage manager\n    s3_uri = s3_storage.upload_file(file_content, str(client_id), str(document_id), file.filename)\n\n    # 1. Store in SQLite for persistence\n    db_doc = DocumentItem(\n        id=document_id,\n        client_id=client_id,\n        project_id=project_id,\n        title=title or file.filename,\n        document_type=document_type or \"PDF\",\n        status=\"active\",\n        version=version,\n        owner=current_user.full_name or current_user.email,\n        visibility=visibility,\n        sha256=sha256_hash,\n        file_size=file_size_str,\n        description=description or \"Cryptographically secured enclave system documentation.\",\n        s3_uri=s3_uri\n    )\n    db.add(db_doc)\n    db.commit()\n    db.refresh(db_doc)\n\n    # 2. Store metadata in GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS as DOCUMENT record (DynamoDB mock)\n    # This keeps our DynamoDB emulator table synchronized immediately.\n    item_data = {\n        \"id\": document_id,\n        \"project_id\": project_id,\n        \"title\": title or file.filename,\n        \"document_type\": document_type or \"PDF\",\n        \"status\": \"active\",\n        \"version\": version,\n        \"owner\": current_user.full_name or current_user.email,\n        \"visibility\": visibility,\n        \"sha256\": sha256_hash,\n        \"fileSize\": file_size_str,\n        \"description\": description or \"Cryptographically secured enclave system documentation.\",\n        \"lastUpdated\": datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat(),\n        \"s3_uri\": s3_uri\n    }\n    portal_item = portal_items_repo.create_item(\"DOCUMENT\", str(client_id), item_data)\n\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"message\": \"Document uploaded successfully.\",\n        \"document\": portal_item.to_dict()\n    }\n\n\n@router.get(\"/download/{id}\")\ndef download_document(\n    id: int,\n    db = Depends(get_db),\n    current_user: User = Depends(get_current_user)\n):\n    \"\"\"\n    Downloads file from S3 bucket with strict boundary permissions.\n    \"\"\"\n    documents = portal_items_repo.list_items(\"DOCUMENT\")\n    doc = next((d for d in documents if str(d.id) == str(id)), None)\n    if not doc:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=status.HTTP_404_NOT_FOUND,\n            detail=\"Document not found.\"\n        )\n\n    # Non-admin boundary validation\n    if current_user.role not in [\"admin\", \"gff_admin\"]:\n        if str(doc.client_id) != str(current_user.client_id):\n            raise HTTPException(\n                status_code=status.HTTP_403_FORBIDDEN,\n                detail=\"Access denied. You do not have permission to download this document.\"\n            )\n\n    try:\n        # Fetch actual bytes from S3/mock store\n        file_content = s3_storage.download_file(str(doc.client_id), str(doc.id), doc.title)\n    except FileNotFoundError:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=status.HTTP_404_NOT_FOUND,\n            detail=\"Document file not found in storage.\"\n        )\n    except Exception as e:\n        raise HTTPException(\n            status_code=status.HTTP_500_INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR,\n            detail=f\"Storage driver exception: {str(e)}\"\n        )\n\n    return Response(\n        content=file_content,\n        media_type=\"application/octet-stream\",\n        headers={\"Content-Disposition\": f\"attachment; filename={doc.title}\"}\n    )\n"}}}
