{"ts":"2026-06-27T21:52:29.371Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Investigating 404 Error**\n\nI've hit a snag. The `assert` statement is failing because the status code is 404, not 200, when attempting to download. I'm now digging into the `download_document` route within `backend/app/api/routes` to pinpoint the cause of this \"Not Found\" error.\n\n\n**Analyzing Document Logic**\n\nI'm now focusing on document retrieval within `/documents.py`. The 404 error seems to stem from a missing document. Specifically, `doc` might be None, or `s3_storage.download_file` might be failing. I'm reviewing the upload process, and realized that `file.filename` becomes the default `title` if a title isn't provided, so the `doc.title` might be `\"Apex Statement of Work Executed\"` and not the original filename from the S3 upload.\n\n\n**Clarifying Storage and Retrieval**\n\nI've got it! The core issue revolves around mismatched filenames between upload and download. S3 stored the document as `\"apex_contract_2026.pdf\"`, yet the retrieval code was using `\"Apex Statement of Work Executed\"`. My thought is to always use the original filename, `file.filename`, for both S3 storage and retrieval. I think the original filename can also be stored as a field on the document metadata for consistency. Using `file.filename` as the key/name in S3 is the simplest solution.\n\n\n**Refining Filename Handling**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on filename inconsistencies and database fields. I realize `app/portal/documents/page.tsx` uses `apiDoc.title || apiDoc.name`, and the actual displayed document name is often the filename. I think I've confirmed that the critical part is ensuring the stored filename is consistent with the retrieval key. I'm checking the `document_item.py` model, and I've reviewed the `upload_document` flow. I'm focusing on preserving or inferring the filename from `file.filename` or `title` fields.\n\n\n**Implementing Filename Consistency**\n\nI'm now making final adjustments to ensure consistent filename handling across upload and download. I've updated the `DocumentItem` schema to include a `filename` field, which I'm populating from the original uploaded file's name. I'm storing this in both the SQLite database and S3 for direct retrieval. Also, I'm making sure that the retrieval code prioritizes `filename` for locating files in S3. I'm handling the fallback cases where `filename` might be missing. I need to make sure the change is reflected in the DynamoDB as well.\n\n\n"}}
