{"ts":"2026-06-27T21:54:50.498Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"rxzmxoy3","input":{"summary":"I have successfully implemented S3 document upload and download support for the GFF AI portal with strict tenant isolation, fully aligned with the existing database and route structures.\n\nHere is a summary of the steps taken:\n1. Created an abstract S3 Storage Manager under `backend/app/services/s3_storage.py` that handles file operations on S3 using `boto3` in production environments, and gracefully falls back to local disk storage in development environments or when credentials are missing.\n2. Expanded the `DocumentItem` SQLite model in `backend/app/models/document_item.py` to store fields such as `filename`, `sha256`, `file_size`, `description`, and `s3_uri` to ensure complete alignment between database metadata and physical storage parameters.\n3. Enhanced the local DynamoDB emulator's mapping logic in `backend/app/repositories/dynamodb_client.py` (`sync_with_sqlite`) to dynamically sync the new metadata columns from SQLite into DynamoDB items.\n4. Created a comprehensive FastAPI route router in `backend/app/api/routes/documents.py` to manage lists, metadata fetches, multi-part form file uploads (secure S3 transport and ledger sealing with SHA-256), and file streams. Non-admin users are strictly scoped to only access documents matching their assigned `client_id`.\n5. Registered the documents router in `backend/app/api/routes/__init__.py`.\n6. Added a detailed test suite (`test_8_document_upload_and_download_scoping`) to the backend smoke test file `backend/app/test_backend_smoke.py` that verifies admin-scopeless listings, client-scoped filters, secure uploads, multi-tenant boundaries (preventing cross-tenant uploads or downloads), and streaming file transport.\n7. Verified that the test suite runs and passes cleanly with 100% success.\n8. Ran the linter and confirmed everything complies perfectly with no warnings.","verified":true}}}
